The paper discusses the asymptotic analysis of node-based recovery algorithms in the context of compressive sensing, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of random sparse matrices (graphs) in the analysis, which falls under the category of sparse recovery (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the scaling of the signal length and the number of non-zero elements, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also mentions the success threshold of the recovery algorithms, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
